<br>
Anyway, any help is good....So thanx in advance!!! <p><table border=0>
<tr>
<td><img src="http://orbita.starmedia.com/~necronooi/necron.gif"></td><td><font size=+6 face="Comic Sans MS" color="red"><center>KUPO!!</center></font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udynamiteneon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DynamiteNeon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/4/01 9:54:56 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.mangaden.com/pics/bdn1_small.jpg l=100 w=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Person-Object Interaction</span><hr size=1> Well, I think the best approach would be to start off with a horizon line so you have something to help keep the two in proper relation to each other.  <br>
<br>
I would start with the chair first since that's the easiest, and it's positioning with affect the person.  Get at least some guidelines drawn for it and then start working on the putting the person in there.  Just make sure not to put too much detail at first and draw lightly so you can make some quick adjustments and erase if you have to. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubigtyme.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BIGTYME</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/4/01 5:23:20 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.dencity.com/Bigtyme77/bane.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Person-Object Interaction</span><hr size=1> Get a pic of someone sitting in a chair and study it. First of all if you know your anatomy it's easy say you have a person 8 heads high nock off 2 heads and you have the height of them sitting.  <p><center><font face="Impact">
